#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:5
msgid ""
"The `dbg!` macro provides a nicer experience for debugging than `println!`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:15
msgid "If you run this program, you'll see:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:21
msgid ""
"You get the file and line number of where this was invoked, as well as the "
"name and value. Additionally, `println!` prints to the standard output, so "
"you really should be using `eprintln!` to print to standard error. `dbg!` "
"does the right thing and goes to stderr."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:26
msgid ""
"It even works in more complex circumstances. Consider this factorial example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:38
msgid ""
"If we wanted to debug this, we might write it like this with `eprintln!`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:42 src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:51
msgid "\"n: {}\""
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:45
msgid "\"n <= 1\""
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:58
msgid ""
"We want to log `n` on each iteration, as well as have some kind of context "
"for each of the branches. We see this output for `factorial(4)`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:72
msgid ""
"This is servicable, but not particularly great. Maybe we could work on how "
"we print out the context to make it more clear, but now we're not debugging "
"our code, we're figuring out how to make our debugging code better."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:76
msgid "Consider this version using `dbg!`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:88
msgid ""
"We simply wrap each of the various expressions we want to print with the "
"macro. We get this output instead:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/dbg-macro.md:102
msgid ""
"Because the `dbg!` macro returns the value of what it's debugging, instead "
"of `eprintln!` which returns `()`, we need to make no changes to the "
"structure of our code. Additionally, we have vastly more useful output."
msgstr ""
